    "b-isurf-canvas-hero": {
      "id": "b-isurf-canvas-hero",
      "type": "canvas",
      "props": {
        "canvasId": "interaction-surfaces",
        "title": "One state, two readers",
        "view": "one-state-two-readers"
      },
      "children": []
    },
    "pm-mrp81bx4-2839-23vo4v": {
      "id": "pm-mrp81bx4-2839-23vo4v",
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 2
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The Issue"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "pm-mrpfasf5-1-dsblal": {
      "id": "pm-mrpfasf5-1-dsblal",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The issue is that people are trying to fit the same medium to both humans and agents, even though we have very different optimal information consumption methods"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "pm-mrpe42kc-17-869urm": {
      "id": "pm-mrpe42kc-17-869urm",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Humans",
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          }
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "pm-mrpddwdu-766-1z1inz": {
      "id": "pm-mrpddwdu-766-1z1inz",
      "type": "list-item",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Text is a great medium, but people learn and understand much more when you can use multiple senses "
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "pm-mrpddwdu-767-o2h9xx": {
      "id": "pm-mrpddwdu-767-o2h9xx",
      "type": "list-item",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "HTML is good as this allows for making significantly better visualizations"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "pm-mrpddwdu-768-17aomg": {
      "id": "pm-mrpddwdu-768-17aomg",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Agents",
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          }
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "pm-mrpddwdu-769-jbnmhs": {
      "id": "pm-mrpddwdu-769-jbnmhs",
      "type": "list-item",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Excel at text but lacking in the visual space"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "pm-mrpfasf5-2-p1nfqi": {
      "id": "pm-mrpfasf5-2-p1nfqi",
      "type": "divider",
      "props": {},
      "children": []
    },
    "pm-mrpfasf5-3-zz5vtb": {
      "id": "pm-mrpfasf5-3-zz5vtb",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Markdown has been the standard for interacting with agents, and for good reason"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "pm-mrpd2dxn-75-25vx8w": {
      "id": "pm-mrpd2dxn-75-25vx8w",
      "type": "list-item",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Models operate largely in a text based world and simple text system allow for huge gains"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "pm-mrpddwdu-758-bfk1ce": {
      "id": "pm-mrpddwdu-758-bfk1ce",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Markdown is not good for human readers, especially as the size of documents grows"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "pm-mrpddwdu-759-au9dee": {
      "id": "pm-mrpddwdu-759-au9dee",
      "type": "list-item",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "I have found myself many a time just not reading the MD docs at all as the UX for it is terrible"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "pm-mrpddwdu-760-2e5vcv": {
      "id": "pm-mrpddwdu-760-2e5vcv",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Recently HTML or MDX have been touted as the best way to do it, which has merrit, but has flaws"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "pm-mrpddwdu-761-qj4gpg": {
      "id": "pm-mrpddwdu-761-qj4gpg",
      "type": "list-item",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Extra tokens for HTML and no easy way to edit the components"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "pm-mrpddwdu-762-pil9qz": {
      "id": "pm-mrpddwdu-762-pil9qz",
      "type": "list-item",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Similar issue with MDX"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "pm-mrpfkxn0-75-76u4o2": {
      "id": "pm-mrpfkxn0-75-76u4o2",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The key idea we need to accept is that AI and humans consume information differently, so there is no true single medium that is best for both of use."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "pm-mrpddwdu-763-0b5gwr": {
      "id": "pm-mrpddwdu-763-0b5gwr",
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 2
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The Solution"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "pm-mrpfkxn0-76-ty8nul": {
      "id": "pm-mrpfkxn0-76-ty8nul",
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 3
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Canonical Shared State"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "pm-mrpg8ecz-2-cir0id": {
      "id": "pm-mrpg8ecz-2-cir0id",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Every document is a "
        },
        {
          "insert": "doc.json",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " bundle: an id-keyed tree of blocks — the "
        },
        {
          "insert": "data model",
          "attributes": {
            "reference": {
              "kind": "doc",
              "path": "10-system-design/20-data-model/00-overview",
              "label": "data model"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " — serialized to "
        },
        {
          "insert": "canonical bytes",
          "attributes": {
            "reference": {
              "kind": "doc",
              "path": "10-system-design/20-data-model/50-canonical-bytes",
              "label": "canonical bytes"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ". "
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "pm-mrpg8ecz-3-t6poph": {
      "id": "pm-mrpg8ecz-3-t6poph",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "No reader consumes this form directly"
        },
        {
          "insert": ".",
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " "
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "pm-mrpg8ecz-4-cdiuzv": {
      "id": "pm-mrpg8ecz-4-cdiuzv",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "It is built for precision, not reading: stable ids make every block addressable, canonical bytes make every change diffable and testable, and the whole tree is validated on every write."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "pm-mrpddwdu-770-6t9k90": {
      "id": "pm-mrpddwdu-770-6t9k90",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Shared State",
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          }
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "pm-mrpddwdu-771-abom36": {
      "id": "pm-mrpddwdu-771-abom36",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The idea is to have a shared representation of the information, but then different ways to render the information to the desired audience."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "pm-mrpd2dxn-76-pozp6x": {
      "id": "pm-mrpd2dxn-76-pozp6x",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Every document is this system is a one canonical state (an id-keyed block tree) that neither reader touches directly. "
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "pm-mrpddwdu-772-kbyxiv": {
      "id": "pm-mrpddwdu-772-kbyxiv",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "A human meets it as a Notion-style editor: "
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "pm-mrpddwdu-773-gm490u": {
      "id": "pm-mrpddwdu-773-gm490u",
      "type": "list-item",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "direct manipulation, drag, comments, themes. "
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "pm-mrpddwdu-774-2mf1ej": {
      "id": "pm-mrpddwdu-774-2mf1ej",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "An agent meets it as rendered MDX through the CLI"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "pm-mrpddwdu-775-lyb5t9": {
      "id": "pm-mrpddwdu-775-lyb5t9",
      "type": "list-item",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "stable, greppable, precisely addressable"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-isurf-intro-2": {
      "id": "b-isurf-intro-2",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "One idea underpins everything else in this system: a document is a single canonical state with two kinds of readers, and each reader gets a surface engineered for how it consumes. A human should never have to read storage bytes; an agent should never have to drive a UI. Both work on the same truth, through the form that is optimal for them."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-isurf-human-heading-6": {
      "id": "b-isurf-human-heading-6",
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 2
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The human interaction surface"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-isurf-human-editor-7": {
      "id": "b-isurf-human-editor-7",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "A human meets a document as a Notion-style editor in the "
        },
        {
          "insert": "workbench",
          "attributes": {
            "reference": {
              "kind": "doc",
              "path": "20-implementation/20-workbench",
              "label": "workbench"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ", rendered by "
        },
        {
          "insert": "docs-viewer",
          "attributes": {
            "reference": {
              "kind": "doc",
              "path": "10-system-design/50-packages/40-docs-viewer",
              "label": "docs-viewer"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ". Blocks appear as rich components — highlighted code, tables, callouts, media, embeds — and editing is direct manipulation: typing with markdown input rules, a slash menu for insertion, drag to reorder, marks for emphasis. Every edit becomes a typed operation against a block id, autosaved and broadcast live to other views."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-isurf-human-embed-8": {
      "id": "b-isurf-human-embed-8",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The surface is embeddable and themable by design: a small set of core building blocks with an open token contract — see "
        },
        {
          "insert": "theming",
          "attributes": {
            "reference": {
              "kind": "doc",
              "path": "20-implementation/40-theming/00-overview",
              "label": "theming"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " — so the same document renders in the workbench, an exported site, or any host page, and can be restyled without touching component code."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-isurf-agent-heading-9": {
      "id": "b-isurf-agent-heading-9",
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 2
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The agent interaction surface"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-isurf-agent-read-10": {
      "id": "b-isurf-agent-read-10",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "An agent meets the same document as rendered markdown. "
        },
        {
          "insert": "docs render <path>",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " prints it; "
        },
        {
          "insert": "docs grep <term>",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " searches every doc as its render. The render is deterministic and pinned byte-for-byte by golden tests, which makes it a contract: an agent never parses "
        },
        {
          "insert": "doc.json",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ", and never has to."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-isurf-agent-write-11": {
      "id": "b-isurf-agent-write-11",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Writing is typed operations, not text patches: the "
        },
        {
          "insert": "mutation model",
          "attributes": {
            "reference": {
              "kind": "doc",
              "path": "10-system-design/40-mutation-model",
              "label": "mutation model"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " addresses blocks by id, with hash preconditions and draft locks so concurrent editors fail loudly instead of clobbering each other. Discovery is built in — "
        },
        {
          "insert": "GET /api/blocks",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " enumerates every block type and the actions it supports, so the available moves are learnable by machine rather than tribal memory."
        }
      ],
      "children": [
        "b-isurf-agent-direction-12"
      ]
    },
    "b-isurf-agent-direction-12": {
      "id": "b-isurf-agent-direction-12",
      "type": "callout",
      "props": {
        "title": "Open direction: a richer agent render",
        "tone": "warning"
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Rendered markdown is the current contract. A richer render — MDX-like, keeping typed structure intact through the trip — is an open direction, deliberately unspecified until it earns its shape. The canonical state makes new renders cheap to add without disturbing existing readers."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-isurf-symmetry-heading-13": {
      "id": "b-isurf-symmetry-heading-13",
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 2
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Symmetry, in practice"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-isurf-symmetry-table-14": {
      "id": "b-isurf-symmetry-table-14",
      "type": "structured-table",
      "props": {
        "columns": [
          "Interaction",
          "Human surface",
          "Agent surface"
        ],
        "rows": [
          [
            "Read",
            "Blocks rendered as rich UI components",
            "Deterministic markdown render (docs render)"
          ],
          [
            "Search",
            "Sidebar tree, backlinks, in-app navigation",
            "docs grep across rendered docs"
          ],
          [
            "Write",
            "Direct manipulation in the editor",
            "Typed block operations via CLI/API"
          ],
          [
            "Safety",
            "Autosave, live updates, single-use undo",
            "Hash preconditions, draft locks"
          ],
          [
            "Discovery",
            "Slash menu and block UI",
            "GET /api/blocks and the docs skill"
          ]
        ]
      },
      "children": []
    },
    "b-isurf-symmetry-para-15": {
      "id": "b-isurf-symmetry-para-15",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Neither column is primary. A feature that improves one surface must not degrade the other; when the two pull in different directions, the canonical state grows whatever structure lets each surface stay optimal — that is the point of keeping state and surface separate."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    }
  }
}
